Boil your kettle and pour the boiling @water{400%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock powder{1} and stir until dissolved - chicken stock made! Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #wide bottomed saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and @chorizo{60%g} to the pan, stir and cook until the chicken is nicely browned all over, ~{5%minutes}. When the chicken is browned, add the shallot, stir and cook for ~{3%minutes} more.

Next add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and the @Arborio rice{175%g}. Stir well to make sure the rice is coated in the fragrant oil. Allow the vinegar to evaporate, then pour in the chicken stock, stir together and bring to the boil. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Pop the #lid{} on (or use some #foil{}) and reduce the heat to medium. Leave the rice to gently simmer, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, do any washing up that needs doing and then finish off the last few bits of prep. Trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop into thirds. Halve the @yellow pepper{1} then remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

After 7 mins, add the pepper and green beans to the pan, on top of the rice (do not stir!), then quickly pop the lid (or foil) back on. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for another ~{10-12%minutes}. The rice is cooked when all of the stock has been absorbed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Taste the rice and season with more salt and pepper if it needs it. Sprinkle over the remaining parsley and add a squeeze of @lemon juice{some}. Put the pan on the table topped with the @lemon wedges{} and let everyone help themselves. Enjoy!